[0.054, "o", "\u001b[1;34m-- the Byte_Encoding is not the privileged resulting encoding"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[2.005, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.002, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;34m----------------------------------\r\n\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m-- Text encoding - Internal checks\r\n\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m----------------------------------\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m/*\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34mCreation of a RexxText\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m*/\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.001, "o", "ooRexx[bash]> "]
[0.805, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;34m/*\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34mNext lines are no longer executed, for 2 reasons:\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m- The method \"TEXT=\" should be declared package-scope but this is not supported by Executor."]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;34m  Not intended to be used by a rexx programmer.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m- The dynamic target changes the string target to a text target, because the argument is a text.\r\n\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m  So the case \"assignment of a text to a string not yet linked to a text\" can no longer occur,\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m  because the dynamic target converts the string to text, which becomes linked to the text.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;34m  The error raised is Object \"hello\" does not understand message \"TEXT=\"\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m*/\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;34m/*\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34ms = \"hello\"\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;34ms~text = .RexxText~new(\"hello\")          -- The counterpart must be a RexxText linked to this String\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34ms~text = .RexxText~new(s)                -- ok, the RexxText is linked to s, now can be assigned to s~text\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;34m*/\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "ooRexx[bash]> "]
