[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;34mNo error because the 2 occurences of the string \"é\" are the same interned string.\r\n\u001b[0m"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;34mSo both texts are in fact the same instance of RexxText.\r\n\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34mThe last encoding selection wins, the result is UTF-8.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
